author: COMSOL
description: This example shows how to run a slope stability analysis of an embankment dam including the pore pressure. The fluid transport in the porous soil is described by Darcy's law, and the elastoplastic analysis is carried out with the Mohr–Coulomb model. The material properties are parameterized with respect to the factor of safety using the shear reduction technique.
